The paper is about a novel network architecture for deep neural networks that is designed to be efficient for mobile devices with limited computational resources. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper introduces a new module called learned group convolution, which is a technique for reducing connections between layers in the network. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories.
